-- Qatar Fund Buys Italy’s Costa Smeralda Resort, Sheikh Hamad Says
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2012-04-16T13:11:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/qatar-fund-buys-italy-s-costa-smeralda-resort-sheikh-hamad-says.html
Italy’s Costa Smeralda resort area
on the island of Sardinia has been bought by Qatar’s investment
fund, Qatar’s Emir  Sheikh Hamad  bin Khalifa Al Thani said.  “We have invested in Sardinia given the importance of the
area,” Sheikh Hamad said at a news conference in Rome today
with Prime Minister Mario Monti. “I can ensure that the Italian
side will be happy about our investment.”  He gave no further details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lorenzo Totaro in Rome at 
